<br />memory protection issues like QNX does then you can make _other_ things <br />faster too - it's not just the TLB invalidation that costs you.<br /><br />(For example, the kernel entry can be much cheaper if you know there are <br />no protection issues to worry about etc etc)<br /><br />So expect switches between cloned processes to be faster, but don't <br />expect them to be no cost at all. The fastest way to context switch is <br />always to do it from user mode directly.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
